work, our model incorporating the acclimatory mechanisms of vegetation under climate
change is used to predict the transmission dynamics of malaria. Model results indicate the
opposing effects of elevated [CO
] and air temperature increase on the dynamics of malaria.
Given the complexity of malaria transmission under environmental disturbances, these effects
would play an important role to better understand how malaria will be likely altered under cli-
mate change, thus contributing to the intervention of this disease.
